  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nThe Vyper compiler [has an option to pass in the version of the EVM to use](https://vyper.readthedocs.io/en/stable/compiling-a-contract.html#setting-the-target-evm-version), but as best I can tell we don't have any way to pass in that option like we do with solc, where you can put it in the solc settings in the config.\r\n\r\nNote, although this is also a separate thing: We may want to start using the Vyper JSON interface?  That may not work with older versions of Vyper; as best I can tell it was only added in v0.1.0-beta.13.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.1.54",
